Here are the steps: 
1) Create your base class (let's call it `List`). This could be a generic list if you want something more flexible than ArrayList for example. It should have methods that all lists will need, like add(), remove() etc... The superclass List is left empty because we are not delegating any functionality to the parent or delegate class in this case (i.e., it's already our base).
